      },
      "date": "2017-06-01 20:56:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe client should also send the atime to the OSS with RPCs, even if they are not written to disk, so that other clients accessing the file will get updated time stamps. Otherwise, if files are being opened and read, but not closed, any client doing a stat() on the file will not see an updated atime.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
